    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted given that ASTM F1717 mandates a single standardized worst-case loading configuration for regulatory submissions, and the conservative nature of this configuration bounds clinical loading. All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percentage difference < 10%). Overall credibility is sufficient to support the medium-risk COU decision. Package conforms to ProfileMinimal; digital signature workflow is pending notarization and will be appended prior to regulatory submission.",
